Generate typos using multiple methods

generate_typos.Rd

This is a simple wrapper to let users generate typos using multiple methods in a single function call. Results returned by this function should be equivalent to the union of all functions supplied to methods.

generate_typos(vec, methods, chars = NA)

Arguments

vec

A vector of strings to attempt to generate typos for.
methods

A vector of strings matching the methods (listed in typo_generation) to use for typo generation.
chars

Characters to use in generating typos. If set to NA, will use the default character sets for each method; otherwise, chars[[i]] should be a character set usable by methods[[i]].

Value

A named list of length length(vec) containing all unique permutations from the typo-generating methods.

Examples

generate_typos(c("Michael", "David"), c("typo_addition", "typo_prefix"))
